name: Alex Pearce
summary: Fremantle Dockers captain Alex Pearce has paid an emotional tribute to his late teammate Cam McCarthy, dedicating a crucial goal to him in a dramatic AFL draw against Collingwood. Pearce fought back tears after the match, saying he had been thinking about McCarthy throughout the game. The goal, which came in the final minutes, helped the Dockers snatch a tie after they had trailed by 28 points at one stage. Pearce's emotional tribute to McCarthy was a reminder of the close bond the players shared. McCarthy, who died at the age of 27 in September 2023, had been a popular figure at the club and his loss has been deeply felt by his teammates and the wider football community.
